1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper primarily focuses on security threats and proposes a security measure to enhance the security of cyber-physical systems. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses cyber-physical systems and their day-to-day operations, which fall under the purview of systems and control. 
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The proposed security measure may involve software engineering techniques to implement the hybrid monitor in cyber-physical systems. 
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the impact of computing and technology on society, particularly in the context of cyber-physical systems. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The proposed monitor may involve the use of AI techniques to detect and prevent cyber-physical attacks.
